## Bonus: Pattern Matching

Use pattern matching to bind the `"Exit!"` string to an `exit` variable.

```elixir
maze = %{
  "south" => %{
    "east" => %{
      "south" => %{
        "west" => %{
          "south" => %{
            "west" => %{
              "south" => %{
                "east" => %{
                  "south" => "Exit!"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

exit = maze["south"]["east"]["south"]["west"]["south"]["west"]["south"]["east"]["south"]
exit
```

## BONUS: Create Your Own Maze

Generate a maze using the [Online Maze Generator](https://www.mazegenerator.net/). It should be
at least a 5 * 5 in width and height.

* Create a deeply nested map to represent your `custom_maze`. It should have an `"Exit!"` value at the end.
* Have a partner navigate your maze using either **map[key]** notationor **map.key** notation to retrieve the `"Exit!"` value.

Enter your solution below.

<!-- livebook:{"break_markdown":true} -->

![](images/5%20by%205%20orthogonal%20maze.png)<!-- Learn more at https://mermaid-js.github.io/mermaid -->

```elixir
maze2 = %{
  west: %{
    south: %{
      east: %{
        north: %{
          east: %{
            south: %{
              west: %{
                south: "Exit!"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

maze2.west.south.east.north.east.south.west.south
```

